column5: Now that winter is here I find myself fishing less and spending more time indoors. What a perfect time to find new music & listen to some tracks from the past. I even pick up the old dusty acoustic in the corner and learn some new songs.  How about you...what are you listening to these days?  I've been listening to Bon Iver for a bit now and can't get enough:       Highdrifter got me on to Jose Gonzalez:    http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=v3LLoUnJl0s   Going way back...there's Son House. Something about 1 man, a chair and a guitar just gets me right. (The White Stripes also do a version of this song)
'tis the season:  a holiday song: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jd4RFPP
i am partial to the sweet sounds of the ice cracking and popping

Good call on Bon Iver.  Excellent stuff.  If you're into that kind of stuff, I suggest Fleet Foxes, particularly these two tracks.  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eRfBqoGVFXc  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7m8CkxXhPtw
Another excellent choice.  I was planning on busting out his Close to Paradise album tonight, actually.
Some More:  Andrew Bird:     The Acorn:
This is, of course, the best answer possible.
At the moment I'm partial to this   Or some TSO

if you can handle a little something more classical, some great voices one this.
